:"/subject/Multi-threaded%20programming/","title":"Multi-threaded programming"},{"id":"DirectX","path":"/subject/DirectX/","title":"DirectX"}]}},{"node":{"title":"Working with Brushes - NinjaTrader 8 Help Guide","path":"/content/work/working-with-brushes-ninja-trader-8-help-guide/","date":"June 2016","timeToRead":1,"description":"NinjaTrader used two different APIs for rending UI components, depending on the performance required. This often caused confusion between the types of .NET objects used for certain tasks, and also required a little bit of guidance to help developers understand some of the multi-threaded implications of using certain types across the life cycle of each object.","content":"\n","cover_image":"/work/images/brushes.png","company":"NinjaTrader LLC","tags":[{"id":"Technical writing","path":"/tag/Technical%20writing/","title":"Technical writing"}],"subjects":[{"id":"NinjaTrader","path":"/subject/NinjaTrader/","title":"NinjaTrader"},{"id":"DirectX","path":"/subject/DirectX/","title":"DirectX"}]}},{"node":{"title":"Using SharpDX for Custom Chart Rendering - NinjaTrader 8 Help Guide","path":"/content/work/using-sharp-dx-for-custom-chart-rendering-ninja-trad/","date":"June 2016","timeToRead":1,"description":"NinjaTrader 8 Charts used a .NET Library called SharpDX that worked with the native Microsoft DirectX API. This was a major overhaul from the previously used GDI namespace and in efforts to help provide better for support for custom chart rendering, I was tasked with designing a tutorial to help users understand the new information that came along with the updated requirements.","content":"\n","cover_image":"/work/images/sharpdx.png","company":"NinjaTrader LLC","tags":[{"id":"Technical writing","path":"/tag/Technical%20writing/","title":"Technical writing"}],"subjects":[{"id":"DirectX","path":"/subject/DirectX/","title":"DirectX"}]}},{"node":{"title":"Drawing Tools - NinjaTrader 8 Help Guide","path":"/content/work/drawing-tools-ninja-trader-8-help-guide/","date":"May 2015","timeToRead":1,"description":"When looking at technical financial data, it's common to need to annotate certain data points on the chart that can be saved and shared for others - we took this approach one step further and extended access to our class of \"Drawing Tools\" to allow users to develop unique drawing tools, building off the concepts we designed to implement the standard set of tools that came with the platform. This was the API Reference that enabled a developer to start using this group of methods and types.","content":"<p><img class=\"g-image g-image--lazy g-image--loading\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml,%3csvg fill='none' viewBox='0 0 1552 1076' xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' xmlns:xlink='http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink'%3e%3cdefs%3e%3cfilter id='__svg-blur-5cbf47dc5f7acb535c4a498763220371'%3e%3cfeGaussianBlur in='SourceGraphic' stdDeviation='40'/%3e%3c/filter%3e%3c/defs%3e%3cimage x='0' y='0' filter='url(%23__svg-blur-5cbf47dc5f7acb535c4a498763220371)' width='1552' height='1076' xlink:href='data:image/png%3bbase64%2ciVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAEAAAAAsCAIAAABaPSmoAAAACXBIWXMAAAsSAAALEgHS3X78AAAJNElEQVRo3s2Zy28kRx3H/V8gEQQ5cObChQN/AAdAqyghWjZLQCAFISFx47HAJeLGAQlukYgiRXCKkEi0SnZREALt2h6P32uPH%2bPxTE/Po9/T3TM90zPTw6fqZ7fHznrWzq53/VOpXFVd012/9/dXnrPrRmBbnU4Q%2bF7Hcbx63a3V/Lrpt9v7e/ter7f0pz9/9O0bn/74rfu3f3T3xmt3b7x6/40ffvL6rY9fu/nvn/z071/7%2brsvvfzel79K/%2b4Xv3Ll7aWX//qFL3303Vf%2b%2ba3v3H3le%2b9/45tzbuWwvbUd%2bUG31%2bv2kl6/30uSKI5ptm3Habrx/t/%2b%2b/NfPPzlnfnf/G7hzu/p53/924e/usPK0tt/%2bM9bP7t38w1Y%2btd0u30yvn96cXpnPr73/R9cqn1y8/a9W2/ev/XmP159fc44qNTKZduyOG6z2Wy32wyiKAqCIEQvnTBwHHN%2bwVwstNY3kihK4rgXRarF8aDbTZIkHQ7TNB0MBmqg2yDVJAN5mqZ9veFohcHU/snlKcsy%2bu3t0tzG5mahWFxdXd3Y2FheXl7QVK1Wu91ujB6iOOh02pZVN%2bv1utm0rJZtG81m3VRzx3X3y%2bWGJqatVqvZavGoVquJLBpNRfSm3iBTU%2b83ajVTE%2bvj8fjzMbBULM6VSqW1tbWdnZ319XU%2b6bouGrAsK9YURnHk%2b4lRH9h2v9kcWNbQ8xOzMe4PJi%2bUhIHi8vLc4eFhsViEh5WVlXK53O%2bjakVHGohjz3Z2C4Wd4vLW4uLWwkJle2uvUCiXSqgFRcFq/ronffPUn2fGwObmJ